Use KPI dashboard to view metrics across different metric categories on one screen. *Scroll down or maximize for dashboard info...*

- jump back to overview of all subsystems in a group with `Links: subsystem view` widget
- limit/extend subsystems shown on this screen using `Selector: subsystems` widget
- use `Dashboard links` or section headers to jump between types of metrics
- focus on time range by setting a range in one of the graphs or using Time/Date/Refresh selector
- apply filters & constraints with KQL or Lucene using Search field

KPI and drill-down dashboards are are primarily designed to show information about a single SSID. You can combine multiple SSIDs from same DSG or even different DSGs using `Selector: subsystems` and  `Search`, but consider the aggregations used in visualizations, for instance "Latest", "Max, "Min" might not always be accurate.
